cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.DC, cs.CC, cs.DL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the computation of the Longest Common Prefix (LCP) Array, which is a fundamental data structure used in string algorithms. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the LCP Array is used in text indexing and search engines. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possibility as the paper mentions the merging of BWTs of two collections, which can be parallelized. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper discusses the time and space complexity of the algorithms. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is a possibility as the paper deals with processing large collections of short reads, which is relevant to the field of bioinformatics and genomics.
